From: Mitchell Augustin <mitchell.augustin@canonical.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:10:39 -0500
Subject: remote-desktop: Correctly handle nullable error from
 secret_collection_for_alias_sync

secret_collection_for_alias_sync can return NULL, so we must handle this case:
https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libsecret/-/blob/ed63e1a96851dcd6bd90abbec5b2b1999afabdc6/libsecret/secret-collection.c#L2205

Fixes: 5940af5b ("remote-desktop, desktop-sharing: Handle when keyring is locked")
Bug-Ubuntu: https://launchpad.net/bugs/2000063
Forwarded: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-control-center/-/merge_requests/3362
Applied-upstream: 51~alpha, commit:0652652b
---
 panels/system/remote-desktop/cc-desktop-sharing-page.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/panels/system/remote-desktop/cc-desktop-sharing-page.c b/panels/system/remote-desktop/cc-desktop-sharing-page.c
index e10c56f..4b4e285 100644
--- a/panels/system/remote-desktop/cc-desktop-sharing-page.c
+++ b/panels/system/remote-desktop/cc-desktop-sharing-page.c
@@ -461,7 +461,7 @@ unlock_gnome_keyring (CcDesktopSharingPage *self)
                                                  NULL, &error);
   if (!collection)
     {
-      g_debug ("Can't load secret collection: %s", error->message);
+      g_debug ("Can't load secret collection: %s", error ? error->message : "No such collection");
       return;
     }
 
